article.description: Army comes from behind to beat Loyola (Md) 77-71
article.headline: Army comes from behind to beat Loyola (Md) 77-71
article.linkText: Army comes from behind to beat Loyola (Md) 77-71
article.story: BALTIMORE -- Kyle Wilson scored 19 of his 25 points after halftime -- including 9 of 10 free throws -- as Army rallied past Loyola (Maryland) late in the second half to win 77-71 Saturday. The Black Knights (11-10, 7-3 Patriot League) survived a late scare from the Greyhounds (9-12, 4-6). Army was trailing until less than 6 minutes remained when Kevin Ferguson (15 points, five blocks) nailed a pair of free throws to take a 58-57 lead. Wilson added a pair from the line along with a 3-pointer and Army led by as many as 12 in the final 2 minutes, hitting 12 straight free throws at one point and making 20 of 25 in the half. Jarred Jones and R.J. Williams launched a flurry in the final 45 seconds that pulled the Greyhounds within 72-70 on a Williams 3-pointer Jones scored 17, Dylon Cormier 14 and Williams 10 for Loyola.
